    "body": "### Related\n\n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/38062\n\n### Problem\n\n`nvim_exec2([[echon '1234567']]` shifts the column of the **next** output value.\n\nAdditional info:\n- Only the first column is shifted.\n- `:echo` is unaffected.\n- Happens only with `nvim_exec2(..., { output = true })`.\n- Shift depends on how many characters were printed before.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```lua\nrequire(\"vim._core.ui2\").enable()\nvim.api.nvim_exec2([[echon '1234567']], { output = true })\nlocal out = vim.api.nvim_exec2(\"hi VisualNC\", { output = true })\nvim.print(out.output) -- VisualNCxxx cleared\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n```\nVisualNC       xxx cleared\n```\n\ninstead of\n\n```\nVisualNCxxx cleared\n```\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev-353+g18d2b5dc43\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Btw\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.17.0 (94e7c887)\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
